Toyota to Raise Turkish Plant Capacity to 210,000, Aksam Reports

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 
2011-03-21T09:48:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-21/toyota-to-raise-turkish-plant-capacity-to-210-000-aksam-reports.html
  Toyota Motor Corp. (7203)  will raise
annual capacity at its Sakarya plant in northwestern  Turkey  to
210,000 units from 170,000 units by introducing new models,
Aksam newspaper reported, citing Orhan Ozer, chief executive of
Toyota Turkey.   Toyota will restart manufacturing the Corolla model and
stop producing the Auris model in Turkey in 2012, the Istanbul-
based newspaper quoted Ozer as saying. The Sakarya plant will
continue to make Toyota Versos and eyes another model as well,
Ozer said, according to Aksam. Toyota Turkey expects annual
production to rise to more than 150,000 cars in 2013, Aksam
said.   Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
